-- Vinals Says Libor Scandal Undermines Trust in Benchmarks
-- B y   S a n d r i n e   R a s t e l l o   a n d   I a n   K a t z
-- 2012-07-16T14:41:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-16/vinals-says-libor-scandal-undermines-trust-in-benchmarks.html
The most serious consequence of
Libor manipulation is it “undermines the certainty and the
trust that markets have on benchmarks,” the director of the
International Monetary Fund’s monetary and capital markets
department said.  Jose Vinals said the Libor-rigging scandal also shows the
importance of completing an overhaul of financial regulations.
He spoke at a news conference in  Washington  today.  To contact the reporters on this story:
